HEADWORD: Sportula
<hw>Spor"tu*la</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ocir⟧r"t⟦usl⟧*l⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Sportulae</plw>
<pr>(-l⟦emac⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>A gift; a present; a
prize; hence, an alms; a largess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To feed luxuriously, to frequent sports and theaters, to run for
the <qex>sportula</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sportulary</ent>⟦br⟧
